
- Git hub Commands

Clone a repository, git clone <web_link>
To create a repository from a existing directory, *******
First Create a new repository on github, GitHub Website
Then copy the link to the repository, Copy Link
Then initialize the repository in the directory, git init
Then link the newly created github repo, git remote add origin <weblink>
Then do a pull to get the README.md file, git pull origin master
Now your branch should be current, yay!
Now to add the files in the directory, git add .
Then make a commit, git commit -m "whatever"
Then pushit back up to github, git push origin master
If for some reason you do this out of order and it comes up with an error that the histories are unrelated, git pull origin master --allow-unrelated-histories
Working with other branches, ********
